The paper deals with topics related to computational complexity (cs.CC) such as polynomial identity testing, as well as topics related to data structures (cs.DS) such as low-dimensional subspaces and hitting sets. It also deals with topics related to information theory (cs.IT) such as compressed sensing and sparse recovery, and topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) such as low-rank recovery. Finally, it deals with topics related to signal processing (cs.SI) such as rank-metric codes.
